06/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Helsinki Committee in Macedonia released a report Wednesday (5 May) that was critical of human rights and freedoms in Macedonia, citing poverty as the cause for most of the abuses. 
The report also criticised the cabinet for neglecting the problems of internally displaced persons and refugees.
In other news Wednesday, Economy Minister Stevco Jakimovski voiced concern over the growth of the underground economy, noting even some large companies are participating. 
Experts estimate the gray economy accounts for as much as 45 per cent of the GDP. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 06/05/04; Makfax, A1 TV - 05/05/04)
